main event: Two round lights (white) were observed in Oxnard, California on March 23, 1957, using binoculars, lasting for 30 seconds.
interesting points: The sighting occurred around 2330 hours and lasted 30 seconds., The weather at the time was overcast., The observer confirmed seeing two objects moving in the northeast direction., Radar detection was attempted but no contact was established., The conclusion from the investigation was insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: An observer who used binoculars to see the lights.
